items.text: Yes, ChatGPT has a free tier. OpenAI offers a free version of ChatGPT that provides access to a range of features and capabilities, including GPT-4o, web browsing, image generation, and more. While a paid subscription, ChatGPT Plus, exists for those seeking advanced features and higher usage limits, the free tier remains a valuable and widely accessible option.

items.title: Here's a more detailed breakdown:
items.text: Free Tier: This tier offers access to the latest model (currently GPT-4o), along with features like web browsing, image generation (with limits), data analysis, and the ability to upload files and photos. ChatGPT Plus : This paid subscription ($20/month) provides users with faster responses, priority access to new features, and higher usage limits. Free Access: OpenAI's mission is to make advanced AI tools accessible to as many people as possible, which is why they offer a free tier. GPT-4o: The free tier provides access to GPT-4o, which includes many of the advanced features previously only available to paid users. Continued Updates: The free version is continuously updated with new features and improvements.
items.markdown:
- **Free Tier:** This tier offers access to the latest model (currently GPT-4o), along with features like web browsing, image generation (with limits), data analysis, and the ability to upload files and photos.[[1]](https://openai.com/index/gpt-4o-and-more-tools-to-chatgpt-free/#:~:text=Bringing%20more%20intelligence%20and%20advanced,helpful%20experience%20with%20Memory%E2%81%A0)[[2]](https://www.zdnet.com/article/is-chatgpt-plus-really-worth-20-when-the-free-version-offers-so-many-premium-features/#:~:text=Betters%20Picaro%20/%20ZDNET-,1.,referencing%20recent%20conversations%20%28lightweight%20version%29)
- **[ChatGPT Plus](https://www.google.com/search?num=100&sca_esv=b6b9cc2a75ab82a9&hl=en&gl=US&glp=1&q=ChatGPT+Plus&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwi11cyXxv2OAxXv0TQHHWtBKDIQxccNegUIsAQQAQ):** This paid subscription ($20/month) provides users with faster responses, priority access to new features, and higher usage limits.[[1]](https://openai.com/chatgpt/pricing/#:~:text=Everything%20in%20Free,$20/%20month)[[2]](https://www.zdnet.com/article/is-chatgpt-plus-really-worth-20-when-the-free-version-offers-so-many-premium-features/#:~:text=Betters%20Picaro%20/%20ZDNET-,1.,referencing%20recent%20conversations%20%28lightweight%20version%29)[[3]](https://www.cloudeagle.ai/blogs/blog-chatgpt-pricing-guide#:~:text=How%20Much%20Does%20ChatGPT%20Cost,user/month%20if%20billed%20annually.)
- **Free Access:** OpenAI's mission is to make advanced AI tools accessible to as many people as possible, which is why they offer a free tier.[[1]](https://openai.com/index/gpt-4o-and-more-tools-to-chatgpt-free/#:~:text=Bringing%20more%20intelligence%20and%20advanced,helpful%20experience%20with%20Memory%E2%81%A0)[[2]](https://www.zdnet.com/article/is-chatgpt-plus-really-worth-20-when-the-free-version-offers-so-many-premium-features/#:~:text=Betters%20Picaro%20/%20ZDNET-,1.,referencing%20recent%20conversations%20%28lightweight%20version%29)
- **GPT-4o:** The free tier provides access to GPT-4o, which includes many of the advanced features previously only available to paid users.[[1]](https://openai.com/index/gpt-4o-and-more-tools-to-chatgpt-free/#:~:text=Bringing%20more%20intelligence%20and%20advanced,helpful%20experience%20with%20Memory%E2%81%A0)[[2]](https://www.zdnet.com/article/is-chatgpt-plus-really-worth-20-when-the-free-version-offers-so-many-premium-features/#:~:text=Betters%20Picaro%20/%20ZDNET-,1.,referencing%20recent%20conversations%20%28lightweight%20version%29)
- **Continued Updates:** The free version is continuously updated with new features and improvements.[[1]](https://www.scribbr.com/frequently-asked-questions/how-long-will-chatgpt-be-free/#:~:text=You%20just%20have%20to%20sign,chat%20box%20to%20get%20started!)

items.title: How to get Google AI search?

items.text: To get Google's AI-powered search features, you'll need to access "AI Mode" in Google Search. This feature is available through the Google app or by visiting google.com/aimode and searching with AI Mode enabled. You can also find it by tapping the Labs icon (beaker icon) within the Google app or at labs.google.com/arch.

items.title: Here's how to access it:
items.text: 1.  Through the Google App: Open the Google app on your phone and look for the AI Mode option on the home screen. It may be a button or a link below the search bar. 2.  Via Google Search: Go to google.com, enter your search query, and look for the AI Mode option below the search bar. 3.  Using Search Labs: You can also find it within Search Labs, accessed through the Google app or by visiting labs.google.com/arch.
items.markdown:
[**1.** **Through the Google App:** ](https://www.google.com/search?num=100&sca_esv=b6b9cc2a75ab82a9&hl=en&gl=US&glp=1&q=Through+the+Google+App&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwi11cyXxv2OAxXv0TQHHWtBKDIQxccNegUInQUQAw) Open the Google app on your phone and look for the AI Mode option on the home screen.It may be a button or a link below the search bar.[[1]](https://support.google.com/websearch/answer/16011537?hl=en&co=GENIE.Platform%3DDesktop#:~:text=How%20to%20access%20AI%20Mode,Mode%20on%20the%20home%20screen.)[[2]](https://support.google.com/websearch/answer/16329036?hl=en&co=GENIE.Platform%3DAndroid#:~:text=Get%20started%20with%20Search%20Live%20On%20your,Search%20Live%20anytime%2C%20tap%20the%20Live%20.)[[3]](https://support.google.com/websearch/answer/16296315?hl=en&co=GENIE.Platform%3DAndroid#:~:text=Make%20sure%20you're%20signed,to%20google.com/aimode.&text=%2C%20tap%20AI%20Mode%20on%20the%20home%20screen.)
[**2.** **Via Google Search:** ](https://www.google.com/search?num=100&sca_esv=b6b9cc2a75ab82a9&hl=en&gl=US&glp=1&q=Via+Google+Search&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwi11cyXxv2OAxXv0TQHHWtBKDIQxccNegUI2QUQAw) Go to [google.com](http://google.com/) , enter your search query, and look for the AI Mode option below the search bar.[[1]](https://support.google.com/websearch/answer/16011537?hl=en&co=GENIE.Platform%3DDesktop#:~:text=How%20to%20access%20AI%20Mode,Mode%20on%20the%20home%20screen.)[[2]](https://support.google.com/websearch/answer/16296315?hl=en&co=GENIE.Platform%3DAndroid#:~:text=Make%20sure%20you're%20signed,to%20google.com/aimode.&text=%2C%20tap%20AI%20Mode%20on%20the%20home%20screen.)
[**3.** **Using Search Labs:** ](https://www.google.com/search?num=100&sca_esv=b6b9cc2a75ab82a9&hl=en&gl=US&glp=1&q=Using+Search+Labs&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwi11cyXxv2OAxXv0TQHHWtBKDIQxccNegUIzwUQAw) You can also find it within Search Labs, accessed through the Google app or by visiting labs.google.com/arch.[[1]](https://support.google.com/websearch/answer/16011537?hl=en&co=GENIE.Platform%3DDesktop#:~:text=How%20to%20access%20AI%20Mode,Mode%20on%20the%20home%20screen.)[[2]](https://www.youtube.com/shorts/3wSmlGO70z0)

items.title: What you can do with it:
items.text: AI Overviews: Get concise summaries of information from multiple sources, with links to explore further. AI Mode: Engage in more conversational searches, ask follow-up questions, and get more in-depth information on a topic. Deep Search: For more complex questions, try Deep Search, which provides comprehensive, cited reports by reasoning across multiple websites. Agentic capabilities: AI Mode can also help with tasks like finding tickets or making reservations, by analyzing options and helping you complete the purchase. Live Search (with video input): Use Google Lens with live video input to get real-time help with visual searches and have conversations with Search in AI Mode.
items.markdown:
- **AI Overviews:** Get concise summaries of information from multiple sources, with links to explore further.[[1]](https://support.google.com/websearch/answer/13572151?hl=en&co=GENIE.Platform%3DAndroid#:~:text=Get%20%22AI%20Overviews%20and%20more,ask%20your%20question%20out%20loud.)[[2]](https://search.google/ways-to-search/ai-overviews/#:~:text=Find%20what%20you're%20looking,English%20searches%20in%20the%20US)
- **AI Mode:** Engage in more conversational searches, ask follow-up questions, and get more in-depth information on a topic.[[1]](https://www.youtube.com/shorts/3wSmlGO70z0)[[2]](https://search.google/ways-to-search/ai-mode/#:~:text=Research%20made%20easy&text=Ask%20your%20question%20all%20in,explore%20more%20on%20the%20web.&text=For%20questions%20where%20you%20want,Google%20AI%20subscribers%20in%20Labs.&text=Ask%20follow-up%20questions%20to,up%20where%20you%20left%20off.&text=AI%20Mode%20connects%20you%20to,a%20wide%20range%20of%20perspectives.)
- **Deep Search:** For more complex questions, try Deep Search, which provides comprehensive, cited reports by reasoning across multiple websites.[[1]](https://search.google/ways-to-search/ai-mode/#:~:text=Research%20made%20easy&text=Ask%20your%20question%20all%20in,explore%20more%20on%20the%20web.&text=For%20questions%20where%20you%20want,Google%20AI%20subscribers%20in%20Labs.&text=Ask%20follow-up%20questions%20to,up%20where%20you%20left%20off.&text=AI%20Mode%20connects%20you%20to,a%20wide%20range%20of%20perspectives.)
- **Agentic capabilities:** AI Mode can also help with tasks like finding tickets or making reservations, by analyzing options and helping you complete the purchase.[[1]](https://blog.google/products/search/google-search-ai-mode-update/#:~:text=Agentic%20capabilities%2C%20to%20do%20the,a%20seamless%20and%20helpful%20experience.)
- **Live Search (with video input):** Use Google Lens with live video input to get real-time help with visual searches and have conversations with Search in AI Mode.[[1]](https://blog.google/products/search/ai-mode-updates-back-to-school/#:~:text=Get%20real-time%20help%20with,helpful%20links%20on%20the%20web.&text=Search%20Live%20is%20fully%20integrated,the%20AI%20Mode%20Labs%20experiment.)

items.title: Important Notes:
items.text: Incognito Mode: Make sure you are signed in to your Google Account and not using Incognito mode. Availability: AI Overviews and other features may not be available for all searches or in all regions. Turning off AI Overviews: While you can turn off "AI Overviews and more" in Search Labs, it won't disable all AI Overviews as they are part of Google Search, according to Google Help.
items.markdown:
- **Incognito Mode:** Make sure you are signed in to your Google Account and not using Incognito mode.[[1]](https://support.google.com/websearch/answer/13572151?hl=en&co=GENIE.Platform%3DAndroid#:~:text=Get%20%22AI%20Overviews%20and%20more,ask%20your%20question%20out%20loud.)[[2]](https://support.google.com/websearch/answer/16296315?hl=en&co=GENIE.Platform%3DAndroid#:~:text=Make%20sure%20you're%20signed,to%20google.com/aimode.&text=%2C%20tap%20AI%20Mode%20on%20the%20home%20screen.)
- **Availability:** AI Overviews and other features may not be available for all searches or in all regions.[[1]](https://support.google.com/websearch/answer/13572151?hl=en&co=GENIE.Platform%3DAndroid#:~:text=Get%20%22AI%20Overviews%20and%20more,ask%20your%20question%20out%20loud.)[[2]](https://support.google.com/websearch/answer/13572151?hl=en&co=GENIE.Platform%3DDesktop#:~:text=Note:%20Turning%20off%20%E2%80%9CAI%20Overviews,can't%20be%20turned%20off.)[[3]](https://support.google.com/websearch/answer/14901683?hl=en#:~:text=AI%20Overviews%20when%20you%20search,where%20AI%20Overviews%20are%20available.)[[4]](https://dreamina.capcut.com/resource/gemini-ai-image-generator#:~:text=Geographic%20restrictions:%20This%20feature%20does%20not%20work,be%20able%20to%20access%20everything%20it%20offers.)
- **Turning off AI Overviews:** While you can turn off "AI Overviews and more" in Search Labs, it won't disable all AI Overviews as they are part of Google Search, [according to Google Help](https://support.google.com/websearch/answer/13572151?hl=en&co=GENIE.Platform%3DDesktop).[[1]](https://support.google.com/websearch/answer/13572151?hl=en&co=GENIE.Platform%3DDesktop#:~:text=Note:%20Turning%20off%20%E2%80%9CAI%20Overviews,can't%20be%20turned%20off.)

items.title: What is the best AI search engine?

items.text: The best AI search engine depends on individual needs and preferences, but Perplexity AI and Microsoft Copilot are frequently cited as top contenders. Perplexity excels at providing accurate, source-backed answers and is well-regarded for research. Microsoft Copilot, powered by OpenAI's GPT-4, offers a conversational and user-friendly experience. Other strong options include You.com for privacy and customization, Brave Search for privacy-focused searching, and Phind for technical queries.

items.title: How to get the Snapchat AI?

items.text: To access the AI on Snapchat, first, ensure your app is updated. Then, navigate to the chat screen by swiping right from the camera screen. My AI should appear at the top of your chat list. Tapping on it will open the chat interface, where you can begin interacting with the AI.

items.title: Here's a more detailed breakdown:
items.text: 1.  Update Snapchat: Make sure you have the latest version of the Snapchat app installed on your device. 2.  Open the Chat Screen: Swipe right from the Camera screen to access the Chat screen. 3.  Locate My AI: My AI is located at the top of your chat list, identified by a friendly virtual assistant icon. 4.  Start a Conversation: Tap on the My AI icon to open the chat window and begin interacting with the AI.
items.markdown:
[**1.** **Update Snapchat:** ](https://www.google.com/search?num=100&sca_esv=b6b9cc2a75ab82a9&hl=en&gl=US&glp=1&q=Update+Snapchat&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwi11cyXxv2OAxXv0TQHHWtBKDIQxccNegUI9gMQAw) Make sure you have the latest version of the Snapchat app installed on your device.[[1]](https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=-YdmPCx3QU4&pp=0gcJCdgAo7VqN5tD)[[2]](https://www.wikihow.com/Get-Ai-Snapchat#:~:text=Things%20You%20Should%20Know%20*%20Snapchat's%20AI,chat%20list%2C%20try%20updating%20the%20Snapchat%20app.)
[**2.** **Open the Chat Screen:** ](https://www.google.com/search?num=100&sca_esv=b6b9cc2a75ab82a9&hl=en&gl=US&glp=1&q=Open+the+Chat+Screen&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwi11cyXxv2OAxXv0TQHHWtBKDIQxccNegUIwAQQAw) Swipe right from the Camera screen to access the Chat screen.[[1]](https://help.snapchat.com/hc/en-us/articles/13387211401620-How-do-I-access-My-AI-on-Snapchat#:~:text=You%20can%20find%20My%20AI,Was%20this%20article%20helpful?)[[2]](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=01QlhdX_Bv0&t=37)
[**3.** **Locate My AI:** ](https://www.google.com/search?num=100&sca_esv=b6b9cc2a75ab82a9&hl=en&gl=US&glp=1&q=Locate+My+AI&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwi11cyXxv2OAxXv0TQHHWtBKDIQxccNegUInwQQAw) My AI is located at the top of your chat list, identified by a friendly virtual assistant icon.[[1]](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=01QlhdX_Bv0&t=37)
[**4.** **Start a Conversation:** ](https://www.google.com/search?num=100&sca_esv=b6b9cc2a75ab82a9&hl=en&gl=US&glp=1&q=Start+a+Conversation&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwi11cyXxv2OAxXv0TQHHWtBKDIQxccNegUIhwQQAw) Tap on the My AI icon to open the chat window and begin interacting with the AI.[[1]](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=01QlhdX_Bv0&t=37)
